complaints.summary: Foam insulation blows out of windshield defroster vents.  It is much worse when heat and fan are turned on.  The windshield does not properly defrost and passengers are deluged with particulates and large chunks of black foam.  This is a hazard to both breathing and visibility.  Porsche is aware of the problem.  Dealer says owners view as too expensive to fix.  A recent Porsche Club of America newsletter article discusses the problem as a hazard and a paid advertisement pushes an alternative repair.

issues.title: Intermediate Shaft (IMS) Bearing Failure
issues.description: The intermediate shaft bearing can fail catastrophically, causing complete engine destruction. This is a known design flaw in early 987 engines where the single-row ball bearing can seize or disintegrate.
issues.fix_description: Complete engine rebuild or replacement, preventive IMS bearing upgrade with LN Engineering solution
issues.prevention: Regular oil changes, IMS bearing replacement as preventive maintenance around 60k miles

issues.title: Rear Main Seal (RMS) Oil Leak
issues.description: The rear main seal commonly fails, causing significant oil leaks. This issue affects many 987 Boxsters and requires engine removal to properly repair.
symptoms: Visible oil leak at engine/transmission junction
issues.fix_description: Engine removal and rear main seal replacement, often combined with IMS bearing service
issues.prevention: Regular oil changes with proper grade oil, avoid over-revving cold engine

issues.title: Convertible Top Motor Failure
issues.description: The convertible top hydraulic motor commonly fails, preventing proper top operation. The motor overheats and burns out, especially in hot climates.
issues.fix_description: Replace convertible top motor assembly and check hydraulic fluid levels
issues.prevention: Regular top operation, avoid operating in extreme temperatures, service hydraulic fluid

issues.title: Water Pump Failure
issues.description: The plastic impeller water pumps are prone to failure, causing overheating. The impeller can separate from the shaft or crack, leading to coolant circulation issues.
issues.fix_description: Replace water pump with updated metal impeller version, flush cooling system
issues.prevention: Regular coolant changes, monitor temperature gauge, replace pump proactively at 80k miles

issues.title: Door Handle Cable Failure
issues.description: The door handle cables stretch and break over time, making it difficult or impossible to open doors from the outside. This is a common wear item on 987 Boxsters.
issues.fix_description: Replace door handle cable assembly, requires door panel removal
issues.prevention: Gentle operation of door handles, regular lubrication of mechanisms

issues.title: Coolant Expansion Tank Cracking
issues.description: The plastic coolant expansion tank develops cracks over time, leading to coolant leaks. The tank becomes brittle with age and heat cycles.
issues.fix_description: Replace coolant expansion tank and associated hoses, flush cooling system
issues.prevention: Regular cooling system inspections, replace tank proactively at 10+ years

issues.title: HVAC Blower Motor Failure
issues.description: The cabin blower motor commonly fails, resulting in no air circulation through the HVAC system. The motor bearings wear out and seize.
issues.fix_description: Replace HVAC blower motor assembly, check cabin air filter
issues.prevention: Regular cabin filter replacement, avoid running blower on high continuously

issues.title: Oil Separator (AOS) Failure
issues.description: The air-oil separator fails, causing excessive oil consumption and smoke from exhaust. This emissions component separates oil from crankcase vapors.
issues.fix_description: Replace air-oil separator unit and associated vacuum lines
issues.prevention: Regular oil changes, avoid extended high-RPM operation when cold

issues.title: Clutch Slave Cylinder Failure
issues.description: The clutch slave cylinder develops internal seals that fail, causing clutch engagement issues. Fluid leaks internally and externally.
issues.fix_description: Replace clutch slave cylinder and bleed hydraulic system
issues.prevention: Regular brake/clutch fluid changes, avoid riding the clutch

issues.title: Ignition Coil Pack Failure
issues.description: Individual ignition coil packs fail over time, causing misfires and poor performance. The coils are mounted directly on the spark plugs and subject to heat stress.
issues.fix_description: Replace failed coil packs and spark plugs, clear diagnostic codes
issues.prevention: Replace coils and plugs at recommended intervals, use quality parts

issues.title: CV Joint and Boot Failure
issues.description: The CV joints and protective boots wear out, especially on vehicles driven aggressively. The boots crack and allow contamination into the joint.
issues.fix_description: Replace CV joint assembly or reboot if caught early
issues.prevention: Regular inspection of CV boots, avoid aggressive cornering and launches

editorial.tagline: Mid-engine perfection with naturally aspirated soul
editorial.hero_blurb: The 987 Boxster S represents Porsche's mid-engine roadster at its most pure, delivering 310hp of naturally aspirated flat-six fury. This is the sweet spot where accessibility meets genuine sports car DNA.
editorial.essence: The 987 Boxster S is the thinking enthusiast's sports car - offering genuine Porsche engineering in a package that's both approachable and thrilling. With its 3.4L flat-six mounted behind your shoulders, it delivers the kind of balanced, communicative driving experience that makes every journey an event.
editorial.heritage: Born from Porsche's racing DNA and the lessons learned from the original Boxster, the 987 generation refined the formula with improved rigidity, more power, and sharper dynamics. It represented the maturation of Porsche's mid-engine roadster concept.
editorial.design_philosophy: Engineers focused on creating the purest expression of a mid-engine sports car - lightweight, balanced, and responsive. Every component was optimized for the driving experience, from the centralized mass to the perfectly positioned controls.
editorial.motorsport_history: While primarily a road car, the Boxster platform proved its mettle in various racing series including the IMSA Cayman Interseries and club racing, demonstrating the inherent performance potential of the mid-engine layout.
editorial.engine_character: The 3.4L flat-six is a masterpiece of natural aspiration - building power linearly from 1,500 RPM to its 7,200 RPM redline with an intoxicating metallic growl that's uniquely Porsche. It's responsive, rev-happy, and rewards commitment.
editorial.transmission_feel: The 6-speed manual is mechanical perfection with short, precise throws and a clutch that telegraphs exactly what's happening. Each shift is deliberate and satisfying, connecting you directly to the drivetrain.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: Mid-engine balance creates remarkable neutrality and composure. The chassis communicates every nuance of grip and load transfer, allowing you to dance right at the edge of adhesion with complete confidence.
editorial.steering_feel: Hydraulic power steering delivers pure, unfiltered feedback with perfect weight progression. You feel connected to the front wheels through every input, making precise placement effortless and confidence-inspiring.
editorial.brake_confidence: Powerful, progressive brakes with excellent pedal feel and fade resistance. The system inspires complete confidence whether you're trail-braking into a corner or making emergency stops.
editorial.sound_signature: A distinctive flat-six symphony that's both mechanical and musical - from the characteristic startup rattle to the crisp induction noise and metallic exhaust note that builds to a spine-tingling crescendo at redline.
editorial.ideal_owner: Driving purists who value engagement over straight-line speed, weekend warriors seeking genuine sports car thrills, and Porsche enthusiasts wanting an accessible entry into the brand's performance legacy.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Those seeking maximum practicality, straight-line drag strip performance, or all-weather daily driving capability in harsh climates.
editorial.buyers_summary: Look for examples with documented maintenance history, especially IMS bearing updates and regular oil changes. The 987 generation addressed many early Boxster reliability concerns, making it the sweet spot for used Porsche ownership.

pros: More powerful engine than 986
Prettier looks than predecessor
Improved cabin over 986
Interior has held up well after 20 years

expertReviews.verdict: After almost a year of ownership, the 987 Boxster S is highly recommended. It successfully addressed the 986's issues with better styling, more power, and improved interior. Despite being almost 20 years old, it has proven reliable and represents excellent value compared to competitors. The reviewer considers it the finest generation of the definitive modern sports car.

expertReviews.title: 987 Porsche Boxster S | The one you can afford is still amazing...
pros: Exceptional mid-corner grip and balance
Confidence inspiring handling with no learning curve
Lightweight feel (3000 lbs but feels lighter)
Excellent ride quality despite being stiff
Rigid convertible chassis with minimal flex
Analog driving experience
Affordable Porsche that delivers core driving sensations
Perfect size for placing on narrow roads
Traditional sports car with no unnecessary features
cons: Brakes feel unassisted and require getting used to
Not the fastest car in terms of raw numbers
Stock version wouldn't sound or drive quite as well as this modified example
expertReviews.verdict: The 987 Boxster S is an exceptional affordable Porsche that delivers the core driving experience of more expensive models. With around 300hp, 3000lbs, and mid-engine rear-drive layout, it offers monumental grip, perfect balance, and confidence-inspiring handling. The reviewer was immediately impressed after three corners, noting how Porsches have no learning curve and make drivers feel at home instantly. Despite needing brake adjustment and not being the fastest, it represents tremendous value for those seeking an analog sports car experience. Modified tastefully to emulate the Boxster Spider, this example proves that affordable Porsches can still provide deeply satisfying driving without compromise.

Beautiful flat-6 engine sound and induction noise

Classic analog Porsche feel and feedback

Mid-engine balance and handling characteristics

expertReviews.verdict: The 2005 Porsche Boxster S 987 is declared the best deal in the used sports car market, offering genuine Porsche experience with flat-6 sound, excellent handling feedback, and comfortable daily usability for around $25,000. While it has heavier controls than Honda alternatives and typical Porsche maintenance costs, it delivers exotic car feel at accessible pricing in the 'golden era' of analog sports cars.

Fantastic engine sound
Great daily driver capability
Super lightweight at 1,300kg
Solid Porsche build quality
Good fuel economy - 350 miles per tank
Relatively affordable entry point to Porsche ownership
cons: High maintenance costs - could easily spend 5,000 to get perfect

Square rear spoiler design
Air conditioning issues common

expertReviews.verdict: Very positive review of 987.1 Boxster as affordable Porsche entry point. Owner loves using it as daily driver despite 171k miles. 240hp 2.7L engine with 5-speed manual offers great driving experience focused on handling and sound rather than outright speed. Bought for under 5,000, represents good value but requires budget for maintenance. Highly recommended for driving enthusiasts.

expertReviews.title: Is The 987 Porsche Boxster S as Good as a Porsche 911?
pros: Really good and predictable handling
Lightweight and delicate sports car feel
Mid-engine characteristics
Two boots for luggage storage
Great exhaust sound with Top Gear exhaust
Short shift kit improves gear changes
cons: Exhaust drone on motorway at highway speeds
Can cause ear ringing on trips over an hour
Less brutal/purposeful feeling compared to 911
expertReviews.verdict: The 987 Boxster S is described as a lovely lightweight delicate sports car with really good predictable handling and mid-engine characteristics. While it feels less brutal and purposeful than a 911, it would make an excellent companion car. The reviewer concludes that rather than choosing between them, having both a Boxster and 911 would be perfect - the Boxster for convertible lightweight mid-engine driving and the 911 for classic rear-engine characteristics.

expertReviews.title: Is It A Proper PORSCHE?? *987 Boxster S FIRST DRIVE!*
pros: Excellent balance due to mid-engine layout
Distinctive Porsche sound
Confidence-inspiring handling
Well-planted through corners
Smooth power delivery
Takes bumps well despite poor roads
Good build quality and technology
Heated seats and Bose sound system
cons: Sloppy gear shifts
Steering has play at center and high speeds
Less dramatic/raw than some competitors
Open differential limits power delivery
Tire wear issues on inside edges
Power delivery feels less exciting compared to other sports cars
expertReviews.verdict: The 987 Boxster S proves itself as a proper Porsche despite being the 'entry-level' model. The mid-engine layout provides exceptional balance and confidence-inspiring handling that allows drivers to push harder than they would in other cars. While it may lack the drama and raw feel of competitors like the S2000, the smooth 3.2L flat-six delivers its 208hp in a refined manner that works perfectly with the chassis setup. Some issues with gear shift quality and steering play detract from the experience, but overall it's a well-engineered sports car that showcases Porsche's expertise.
